Your popup content starts with:

<div class="popup-container scparts-popup-style">
    <div class="popup-actions">
    ...
    <div class="form-container">
        <form id="scPartsForm">

Notice:

class="popup-container scparts-popup-style"

The popup itself is 866px wide, but the actual form is inside:

.popup-container
.form-container
#scPartsForm

and those classes almost certainly have old width restrictions somewhere else in your CSS.

First debug

Run:

console.log($(".popup-container.scparts-popup-style").width());
console.log($(".form-container").width());
console.log($("#scPartsForm").width());

I suspect one of those will be around 500-600px.

CSS override to force full width

Add this AFTER all existing popup CSS:

/* Stock coded parts popup */

.popup-container.scparts-popup-style {
    width: 100% !important;
    max-width: 100% !important;
    height: 100% !important;
    box-sizing: border-box;
}

.popup-container.scparts-popup-style .form-container {
    width: 100% !important;
    max-width: 100% !important;
    height: calc(100% - 60px) !important;
    box-sizing: border-box;
    overflow-y: auto;
}

.popup-container.scparts-popup-style #scPartsForm {
    width: 100% !important;
    max-width: none !important;
}

/* Stretch rows */
.popup-container.scparts-popup-style .form-row {
    width: 100% !important;
}

/* Stretch controls */
.popup-container.scparts-popup-style .form-group {
    flex: 1 1 auto !important;
}

/* Telerik controls */
.popup-container.scparts-popup-style .k-combobox,
.popup-container.scparts-popup-style .k-dropdown,
.popup-container.scparts-popup-style .k-textbox,
.popup-container.scparts-popup-style .k-numerictextbox {
    width: 100% !important;
}
Second debug (important)

After adding the CSS, run:

console.log("popup", $(".k-window.scparts-popup-style").width());

console.log("container",
    $(".popup-container.scparts-popup-style").width());

console.log("form-container",
    $(".popup-container.scparts-popup-style .form-container").width());

console.log("form",
    $("#scPartsForm").width());

If popup is ~866 but form is still much smaller, then I need to see the CSS definitions for:

.popup-container
.form-container
.form-row
.form-group

because those are the classes actually controlling the layout, not Telerik. The HTML you pasted strongly suggests a custom flex/grid layout is limiting the form width
